<br style="page-break-before:always; clear:both;" /><hr style="border:0; border-top:1px solid #cbd5e1; margin:24px 0;" />

<h4 style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:4pt; page-break-after:avoid;">Table 6.8: Notice Board Collection (<code style="background:#f1f5f9; padding:2px 4px; font-family:Consolas,monospace; font-size:10pt; color:#4c1d95;">notices</code>)</h4>
<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman',serif; font-size:12pt; text-align:justify; margin-bottom:12pt; line-height:1.5;">Stores notifications published by administrators or faculty members:</p>

<table style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%; margin:12pt 0; border:1px solid #000;"><tr style="background-color:#f8fafc;"><th style="border:1px solid #000; padding:6px; background-color:#f1f5f9; font-weight:bold; font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:10.5pt; text-align:left;">Field Name</th><th style="border:1px solid #000; padding:6px; background-color:#f1f5f9; font-weight:bold; font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:10.5pt; text-align:left;">Data Type</th><th style="border:1px solid #000; padding:6px; background-color:#f1f5f9; font-weight:bold; font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:10.5pt; text-align:left;">Key Type</th><th style="border:1px solid #000; padding:6px; background-color:#f1f5f9; font-weight:bold; font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:10.5pt; text-align:left;">Nullable</th><th style="border:1px solid #000; padding:6px; background-color:#f1f5f9; font-weight:bold; font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:10.5pt; text-align:left;">Description / Constraints</th></tr>

<tr><td style="border:1px solid #000; padding:6px; font-size:10pt; font-family:'Times New Roman',serif;"><code style="background:#f1f5f9; padding:2px 4px; font-family:Consolas,monospace; font-size:10pt; color:#4c1d95;">_id</code></td><td style="border:1px solid #000; padding:6px; font-size:10pt; font-family:'Times New Roman',serif;">ObjectId</td><td style="border:1px solid #000; padding:6px; font-size:10pt; font-family:'Times New Roman',serif;">PK</td><td style="border:1px solid #000; padding:6px; font-size:10pt; font-family:'Times New Roman',serif;">No</td><td style="border:1px solid #000; padding:6px; font-size:10pt; font-family:'Times New Roman',serif;">Unique identifier</td></tr>
<tr><td style="border:1px solid #000; padding:6px; font-size:10pt; font-family:'Times New Roman',serif;"><code style="background:#f1f5f9; padding:2px 4px; font-family:Consolas,monospace; font-size:10pt; color:#4c1d95;">title</code></td><td style="border:1px solid #000; padding:6px; font-size:10pt; font-family:'Times New Roman',serif;">String</td><td style="border:1px solid #000; padding:6px; font-size:10pt; font-family:'Times New Roman',serif;">-</td><td style="border:1px solid #000; padding:6px; font-size:10pt; font-family:'Times New Roman',serif;">No</td><td style="border:1px solid #000; padding:6px; font-size:10pt; font-family:'Times New Roman',serif;">Headline of the notice</td></tr>
<tr><td style="border:1px solid #000; padding:6px; font-size:10pt; font-family:'Times New Roman',serif;"><code style="background:#f1f5f9; padding:2px 4px; font-family:Consolas,monospace; font-size:10pt; color:#4c1d95;">content</code></td><td style="border:1px solid #000; padding:6px; font-size:10pt; font-family:'Times New Roman',serif;">String</td><td style="border:1px solid #000; padding:6px; font-size:10pt; font-family:'Times New Roman',serif;">-</td><td style="border:1px solid #000; padding:6px; font-size:10pt; font-family:'Times New Roman',serif;">No</td><td style="border:1px solid #000; padding:6px; font-size:10pt; font-family:'Times New Roman',serif;">Detailed announcement body</td></tr>
<tr><td style="border:1px solid #000; padding:6px; font-size:10pt; font-family:'Times New Roman',serif;"><code style="background:#f1f5f9; padding:2px 4px; font-family:Consolas,monospace; font-size:10pt; color:#4c1d95;">author</code></td><td style="border:1px solid #000; padding:6px; font-size:10pt; font-family:'Times New Roman',serif;">ObjectId</td><td style="border:1px solid #000; padding:6px; font-size:10pt; font-family:'Times New Roman',serif;">FK</td><td style="border:1px solid #000; padding:6px; font-size:10pt; font-family:'Times New Roman',serif;">No</td><td style="border:1px solid #000; padding:6px; font-size:10pt; font-family:'Times New Roman',serif;">References <code style="background:#f1f5f9; padding:2px 4px; font-family:Consolas,monospace; font-size:10pt; color:#4c1d95;">User._id</code></td></tr>
<tr><td style="border:1px solid #000; padding:6px; font-size:10pt; font-family:'Times New Roman',serif;"><code style="background:#f1f5f9; padding:2px 4px; font-family:Consolas,monospace; font-size:10pt; color:#4c1d95;">targetRoles</code></td><td style="border:1px solid #000; padding:6px; font-size:10pt; font-family:'Times New Roman',serif;">Array</td><td style="border:1px solid #000; padding:6px; font-size:10pt; font-family:'Times New Roman',serif;">-</td><td style="border:1px solid #000; padding:6px; font-size:10pt; font-family:'Times New Roman',serif;">No</td><td style="border:1px solid #000; padding:6px; font-size:10pt; font-family:'Times New Roman',serif;">Enum list: <code style="background:#f1f5f9; padding:2px 4px; font-family:Consolas,monospace; font-size:10pt; color:#4c1d95;">['student', 'faculty', 'admin']</code></td></tr>
</table>
<br style="page-break-before:always; clear:both;" /><hr style="border:0; border-top:1px solid #cbd5e1; margin:24px 0;" />

<h3 style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:13pt; font-weight:bold; margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:6pt; page-break-after:avoid;">6.3 Database Indexing &amp; Uniqueness Constraints</h3>
<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman',serif; font-size:12pt; text-align:justify; margin-bottom:12pt; line-height:1.5;">1.  <strong>Users:</strong> Unique index on <code style="background:#f1f5f9; padding:2px 4px; font-family:Consolas,monospace; font-size:10pt; color:#4c1d95;">email</code>. Sparse unique indexes on <code style="background:#f1f5f9; padding:2px 4px; font-family:Consolas,monospace; font-size:10pt; color:#4c1d95;">studentId</code> and <code style="background:#f1f5f9; padding:2px 4px; font-family:Consolas,monospace; font-size:10pt; color:#4c1d95;">facultyId</code> allow these fields to be optional for admins while enforcing uniqueness for other roles.</p>
<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman',serif; font-size:12pt; text-align:justify; margin-bottom:12pt; line-height:1.5;">2.  <strong>Academic Records:</strong> Compound unique index on <code style="background:#f1f5f9; padding:2px 4px; font-family:Consolas,monospace; font-size:10pt; color:#4c1d95;">{ student: 1, semester: 1 }</code> prevents duplicate semester records for a student.</p>
<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman',serif; font-size:12pt; text-align:justify; margin-bottom:12pt; line-height:1.5;">3.  <strong>Attendance:</strong> Compound unique index on <code style="background:#f1f5f9; padding:2px 4px; font-family:Consolas,monospace; font-size:10pt; color:#4c1d95;">{ course: 1, date: 1 }</code> restricts attendance entry to once per course per day.</p>
<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman',serif; font-size:12pt; text-align:justify; margin-bottom:12pt; line-height:1.5;">4.  <strong>Submissions:</strong> Compound unique index on <code style="background:#f1f5f9; padding:2px 4px; font-family:Consolas,monospace; font-size:10pt; color:#4c1d95;">{ assignment: 1, student: 1 }</code> limits students to one file upload per assignment.</p>

<br style="page-break-before:always; clear:both;" /><hr style="border:0; border-top:1px solid #cbd5e1; margin:24px 0;" />

<h2 style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:16pt; font-weight:bold; margin-top:24pt; margin-bottom:12pt; border-bottom:2px solid #000; padding-bottom:4pt; page-break-after:avoid;">Chapter 7: Modular Implementation &amp; Workflows</h2>

<h3 style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:13pt; font-weight:bold; margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:6pt; page-break-after:avoid;">7.1 Two-Step Auth &amp; OTP Delivery Workflow</h3>
<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman',serif; font-size:12pt; text-align:justify; margin-bottom:12pt; line-height:1.5;">Authentication in AcadTrack follows a two-step process to secure user sessions:</p>
<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman',serif; font-size:12pt; text-align:justify; margin-bottom:12pt; line-height:1.5;">1.  <strong>Request Login/Signup:</strong> The user submits their credentials. The server verifies the password hashing using <code style="background:#f1f5f9; padding:2px 4px; font-family:Consolas,monospace; font-size:10pt; color:#4c1d95;">bcryptjs</code>.</p>
<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman',serif; font-size:12pt; text-align:justify; margin-bottom:12pt; line-height:1.5;">2.  <strong>OTP Generation:</strong> If the credentials are valid, the server generates a 6-digit OTP code and saves it to the database with a 5-minute expiration window.</p>
<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman',serif; font-size:12pt; text-align:justify; margin-bottom:12pt; line-height:1.5;">3.  <strong>Email Delivery:</strong> The backend connects to the Brevo API to send the OTP to the user's email address.</p>
<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman',serif; font-size:12pt; text-align:justify; margin-bottom:12pt; line-height:1.5;">4.  <strong>Verification:</strong> The user submits the OTP code. If the code is valid, the server generates a JWT to establish the user's session.</p>

<h3 style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:13pt; font-weight:bold; margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:6pt; page-break-after:avoid;">7.2 Student Progress Dashboard &amp; Placement Engine</h3>
<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman',serif; font-size:12pt; text-align:justify; margin-bottom:12pt; line-height:1.5;">The placement eligibility engine calculates student eligibility by analyzing records across multiple collections:</p>
<ul style="margin-bottom:12pt; margin-left:20px;"><li>  <strong>GPA Verification:</strong> The engine reads the most recent semester record to retrieve the CGPA.</li>
<li>  <strong>Backlog Scan:</strong> It checks all course grades in the student's history, flagging any courses with a grade of <code style="background:#f1f5f9; padding:2px 4px; font-family:Consolas,monospace; font-size:10pt; color:#4c1d95;">F</code> as an active backlog.</li>
<li>  <strong>Attendance Aggregation:</strong> The engine retrieves all attendance records for the student across their enrolled courses, calculating their overall attendance percentage.</li>
<li>  <strong>Evaluation:</strong> If the student's CGPA is <span style="font-style:italic;">\ge</span> 7.0, their attendance is <span style="font-style:italic;">\ge</span> 75%, and they have 0 active backlogs, the system marks them as eligible for placement drives.</li>
</ul>
<h3 style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:13pt; font-weight:bold; margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:6pt; page-break-after:avoid;">7.3 Timetable &amp; Schedule Manager Conflict Checks</h3>
<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman',serif; font-size:12pt; text-align:justify; margin-bottom:12pt; line-height:1.5;">The scheduling module manages course timetables and prevents double-booking of classrooms:</p>
<ul style="margin-bottom:12pt; margin-left:20px;"><li>  <strong>Input Validation:</strong> The system checks that the start time is earlier than the end time.</li>
<li>  <strong>Overlap Validation:</strong> When an administrator or faculty member schedules a class, the server queries existing schedule slots for the same day and room.</li>
<li>  <strong>Validation Check:</strong> The system verifies that the new slot's times do not overlap with any existing bookings.</li>
<li>  <strong>Resolution:</strong> If an overlap is detected, the server rejects the request with an error message, helping to coordinate room allocations.</li>
</ul>
<h3 style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:13pt; font-weight:bold; margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:6pt; page-break-after:avoid;">7.4 Faculty Attendance Registry &amp; Grading Workflows</h3>
<ul style="margin-bottom:12pt; margin-left:20px;"><li>  <strong>Attendance Registry:</strong> Faculty members can mark student attendance for specific course dates. The backend enforces unique date entries per course to prevent duplicate records.</li>
<li>  <strong>Grading Workflow:</strong> Faculty submit grades for student assignments. The system calculates GPAs based on course credits and grade points, automatically updating the student's CGPA.</li>
</ul>
<h3 style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:13pt; font-weight:bold; margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:6pt; page-break-after:avoid;">7.5 Assignment Hosting and Notices Modules</h3>
<ul style="margin-bottom:12pt; margin-left:20px;"><li>  <strong>Assignment Hosting:</strong> Faculty can publish assignments with descriptions and reference documents. Students upload their submissions in PDF format, which are saved in the file system with unique paths.</li>
<li>  <strong>Notice Board:</strong> Faculty and administrators can post announcements. These notices are targeted to specific roles (e.g., student or faculty) and are filtered on the client application accordingly.</li>
</ul>
<br style="page-break-before:always; clear:both;" /><hr style="border:0; border-top:1px solid #cbd5e1; margin:24px 0;" />

<h2 style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:16pt; font-weight:bold; margin-top:24pt; margin-bottom:12pt; border-bottom:2px solid #000; padding-bottom:4pt; page-break-after:avoid;">Chapter 8: Security &amp; Reliability Engineering</h2>

<h3 style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:13pt; font-weight:bold; margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:6pt; page-break-after:avoid;">8.1 Role-Based Access Control (RBAC) Middleware</h3>
<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman',serif; font-size:12pt; text-align:justify; margin-bottom:12pt; line-height:1.5;">The application secures API endpoints using custom middleware. After validating the JWT signature, the middleware checks that the user's role matches the authorized roles for that endpoint. For example, grading endpoints are restricted to <code style="background:#f1f5f9; padding:2px 4px; font-family:Consolas,monospace; font-size:10pt; color:#4c1d95;">faculty</code>, user configuration tools are restricted to <code style="background:#f1f5f9; padding:2px 4px; font-family:Consolas,monospace; font-size:10pt; color:#4c1d95;">admin</code>, and assignment submissions are restricted to <code style="background:#f1f5f9; padding:2px 4px; font-family:Consolas,monospace; font-size:10pt; color:#4c1d95;">student</code>.</p>

<h3 style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:13pt; font-weight:bold; margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:6pt; page-break-after:avoid;">8.2 Hashing, Tokens, and Session Security</h3>
<ul style="margin-bottom:12pt; margin-left:20px;"><li>  <strong>Password Encryption:</strong> User passwords are encrypted using <code style="background:#f1f5f9; padding:2px 4px; font-family:Consolas,monospace; font-size:10pt; color:#4c1d95;">bcryptjs</code> before storage, protecting credentials from unauthorized access.</li>
<li>  <strong>Stateless Authentication:</strong> User sessions are managed using JWTs. Tokens include an expiration time of 12 hours, reducing the risk of session hijacking.</li>
<li>  <strong>Database Constraints:</strong> The system uses MongoDB unique indexes to enforce data integrity at the database level.</li>
</ul>
<h3 style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:13pt; font-weight:bold; margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:6pt; page-break-after:avoid;">8.3 File Upload Restrictions &amp; Filter Middleware</h3>
<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman',serif; font-size:12pt; text-align:justify; margin-bottom:12pt; line-height:1.5;">Assignment submissions are processed using <code style="background:#f1f5f9; padding:2px 4px; font-family:Consolas,monospace; font-size:10pt; color:#4c1d95;">multer</code> with strict validation rules:</p>
<ul style="margin-bottom:12pt; margin-left:20px;"><li>  <strong>Type Validation:</strong> Uploads are restricted to PDF documents.</li>
<li>  <strong>Size Limit:</strong> File sizes are capped at 5 MB to prevent resource exhaustion on the server.</li>
<li>  <strong>Filename Sanitization:</strong> Uploaded files are renamed using unique timestamps to avoid file collision and path traversal security vulnerabilities.</li>
</ul>
<br style="page-break-before:always; clear:both;" /><hr style="border:0; border-top:1px solid #cbd5e1; margin:24px 0;" />

<h2 style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:16pt; font-weight:bold; margin-top:24pt; margin-bottom:12pt; border-bottom:2px solid #000; padding-bottom:4pt; page-break-after:avoid;">Chapter 9: Testing &amp; Quality Assurance</h2>

<h3 style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:13pt; font-weight:bold; margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:6pt; page-break-after:avoid;">9.1 Quality Assurance Strategy</h3>
<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman',serif; font-size:12pt; text-align:justify; margin-bottom:12pt; line-height:1.5;">Testing focused on verify core business logic, database constraints, and API access controls. This included checking calculation engines (GPA and attendance), scheduling validations, and route permissions.</p>

<h3 style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:13pt; font-weight:bold; margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:6pt; page-break-after:avoid;">9.2 Modular and Integration Testing</h3>
<ul style="margin-bottom:12pt; margin-left:20px;"><li>  <strong>Conflict Verification:</strong> Tested the scheduling validator to ensure overlapping time entries in the same classroom are correctly rejected.</li>
<li>  <strong>Access Control Verification:</strong> Checked role restrictions to confirm that requests to admin or faculty endpoints without the required role result in access denial.</li>
<li>  <strong>Academic Record Verification:</strong> Verified that the placement engine computes eligibility status flags correctly when student metrics cross the defined thresholds.</li>
</ul>
<br style="page-break-before:always; clear:both;" /><hr style="border:0; border-top:1px solid #cbd5e1; margin:24px 0;" />

<h3 style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:13pt; font-weight:bold; margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:6pt; page-break-after:avoid;">9.3 Comprehensive Test Cases Matrix</h3>
<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman',serif; font-size:12pt; text-align:justify; margin-bottom:12pt; line-height:1.5;">The test matrix outlines the execution outcomes across functional modules:</p>

